description:
In this episode, we learn about the life of Mary Jones. In 1800, Mary Jones longed to own her own Bible, so here we learn about her life as she saved her pennies and walked barefoot for 28 miles through the desolate Welsh countryside. She arrived at the town of Bala, Wales, to make her purchase from Thomas Charles. This story inspired countless others and give impetus to the many fledgling Bible societies and mission movements.
